item.title: Al Seminario
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Perched on a hilltop between Lucca and the coast, Al Seminario offers stunning views and a private location, but is close enough to the highway to make a good base for exploring the rest of Tuscany. Open the windows as you drive up into the hills and follow an unpaved road to the gates of this rustic four-bedroom villa; you??ll know you??re on vacation when you sink into the infinity-edge pool with a panoramic view.
Al Seminario may be in the middle of the countryside, but it doesn??t lack for amenities, starting with the vine-covered pergola that stretches along the front of the house. Dine under the shade of the wisteria at the table and chairs there, or stretch out on a chaise longue by the pool and listen to its waterfall. There??s an outdoor barbecue, too, to make al fresco dining a snap. Inside, there??s Sky cable TV, a ping pong table and, for the smallest travelers, a baby cot and high chair.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: The villa was just awesome. Perfect for relaxation. The pictures in the profile were accurate. I opted for the airport pick up the villa is in a rural residential area away from kuta/seminyak so a taxi might get lost. The villa was very comfortable and pool refreshing. The bedroom is enclosed and a/c while everything else is open so be prepared. Yes I now know what a previous review was talking about rusty water, but you can live with it, don't drink it of course. Breakfast was delicious and you can order food as well. All in all a great stay and definitely worth the money.

We had an amazing stay at Depanas villa. The home is beautiful - looks exactly as it does in the photos and Depana and his team really go out of their way to help you. Had amazing free breakfast every morning, and felt so welcome. Would definitely Go back again, thank you Depana!

item.title: Grape Villa
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded: Stunning Urban Contemporary. For those seeking the best of Urban Living!! Bright, airy open floor plan with 3 full bedrooms and 2 baths. Corner residence with 2 decks facing NorthEast and SouthEast. Contemporary European style kitchen featuring Caesar style counter tops, Fisher & Paykel dual drawer dishwasher and refrigerator. Ge Profile oven, electric range and microwave. Tandem parking for 2 cars. Come see what makes Aria Residence 303 so desirable.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Angelo was a wonderful host who added thoughtful personalized elements to the experience. The house and pool were very clean and the pool was set up in a very inviting way. He provided thorough instructions about how to use the TV and stereo, and he made himself available to answer any questions that might come up. The pool is fabulous, with nice shade and sun areas for sitting.

Honestly, it could not have been more perfect. Angelo was the ideal host, welcoming, gracious and helpful, but not overly meddlesome. His home is lovely, and really idiot-proof for an easy and relaxing vacation. Amazing pool where lights come on as the sun goes down, and a spa that starts bubbling just when it starts to get chilly. The backyard is surrounded by orange trees and the smell of the blossoms is intoxicating. There are signs throughout the house to help with wi-fi, work the sound system, etc. Hard to imagine a more ideal set-up. Thank you, Angelo! We hope to be back soon.
The host was very accommodating and professional. Nice quiet neighborhood and beautiful pool area!

item.title: Mas d'Eyragues
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Prepare to be charmed by the French countryside at Mas d’Eyragues. Set on nearly 7 acres outside Avignon, the villa has endless spots for families to explore, from a pool and pétanque court to a half tennis court and garden. Traditional decor gives the house an element of country chic, and nine bedrooms divided between the main house and guest house mean there’s plenty of room for children of all ages.
There’s plenty to entertain during your stay, from a heated pool, al-fresco shower and jetted tub and outdoor sound system and bar to a pétanque court, half tennis court, swingset, trampoline and ping-pong table. Explore the garden, take the bicycles for a ride, try a local specialty on the barbecue, or relax at the outdoor sitting and dining areas. For evenings and rainy days, satellite TV, Wi-Fi, foosball and pool tables, a fitness room and bar and wine cellar offer plenty of diversions. For comfort and convenience, the villa is air-conditioned and has a fireplace and laundry facilities.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: This is a wonderful house close to nature with a very beautiful views. Depana was so helpful and even prepared breakfast for us at 6.30 a.m.. Unfortunately, we only lived for one night, since our friends came to Bali and we came to them for the next night. If you want to experience local life and hope for a peaceful holiday, this is definitely the best choice.

If anyone looking for a beautiful countryside life, this is the place - except for those sensitive to water quality. Thank you Depana and your lovely wife for making our stay very comfortable with great service at reasonable cost. It was a fantastic memory to stay with you!

item.title: Les Cavaliers
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Les Cavaliers villa is located close to Cevennes National Park, near Uzes in Provence. The area is ideal for enjoying the wonders of nature and the savors of wine. For the outdoorsy types, options for rafting and body rafting, mountain climbing, cave exploration and hunting are also situated near Les Cavaliers. A true marriage of modern luxury and old world charm, your dream French villa awaits!
The marvelous grounds at Les Cavaliers include a tennis court with an elevated and lit lounge area for spectators, two swimming pools??one for adults and one for children, a volleyball course, and a fitness lodge with a climbing wall and a sauna. Ample alfresco dining and lounging areas are also featured on the covered terrace. Use of the mountain and Quad bikes is complimentary??explore the great outdoors! Inside, you will find a home theatre, satellite TV, multiple fireplaces, laptop and Wi-Fi access. Baby equipment is available, and the villa also includes various social games, video games and a children??s playroom.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: The place is so pretty. It is just look the same as the pictures. Depana is a very nice guy. He can well-speak in English and well-explained all the rules. This is the first time a live in a villa. The sound of forest is so good. At night, there are bats flying by. This is the first time I saw a real bat flew in front of me. So amazing!

item.title: Villa Machiavelli
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
The views justify the trip to Italy at Villa Machiavelli. Just 20 minutes outside Florence in the Chianti Classico region, the recently restored 16th-century villa combines splendid Renaissance architecture and interiors with 21st century luxuries, topped off with panoramic views of the countryside. The villa accommodates up to twenty guests, but larger groups can rent the separate vineyard villa for more space.
You??ll feel like Italian nobility at the fully staffed villa, formerly the home of the Machiavelli and Mazzei families. Drive in or use the helipad and explore the vineyards, olive groves and forest on the estate. Work up a sweat in the gym and cool off in the outdoor pool. For entertainment, there??s a piano, satellite TV and Wi-Fi access; for comfort, there??s air conditioning and an elevator.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: We had a lovely stay. The villa was comfortable and the pool was great for a cooling dip. Convenient location to the main street and walking distance to the night food market and beach. There is a 24 hour concierge service and the staff are friendly and provide a great service.

The best villa I've ever stayed in, in bali. It's a very calm place right next to the beach. There are lots of interesting details in the interior and the service. Amazing breakfast!!! Beautiful bed sheets, dishes and impossibly beautiful interior. I'm definitely going to visit again for a longer time!

item.title: Villa Splendida
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Villa Splendida is situated in the exclusive Borgo Egnazia resort, home to our most luxurious Puglia villa rentals. With its spacious private gardens and pool, 3-bedroom Villa Splendida makes a supremely relaxing retreat. Guests enjoy access to a wide range of luxury amenities including two beach clubs on the Adriatic Sea.
One of four adjoining villas, Villa Splendida??s private garden and pool are separated from its neighbors by garden walls. Spread over three floors, you??ll find plenty of space in which to enjoy your splendid surroundings. The layout is comparable to our other Borgo Egnazia villas, however Villa Splendida benefits from a larger pool and garden with gazebo as well as a courtyard on the lower level.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: The villa is just the same as the pictures. The staff are very good at cooking and cook us very delicious breakfast and lunch. Jamie and Wendy are both hospitable and gave us a lot of help. Anyway, everything went well except for the weather. We think we will go back to Italy again during the sunny days.

item.title: Castell de Manresa
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Enjoy Mallorca??s famed sun and sea from your own private estate at Castell de Manresa. Nestled on the bay of Pollensa close to several beaches, the circa-1715 main house boasts spectacular views over the Mediterranean and was recently renovated in modern style. A full staff and eight suite-style bedrooms make the property feel like a private boutique hotel.
During your stay, a cook, waiter and housekeeper will be on hand, leaving you free to relax by the pool or one of several outdoor lounge areas overlooking the sea. Work on your game on the tennis court or your routine in the gym, indulge in a sauna session or steam bath, and enjoy local fare from the barbecue at the al-fresco dining area. Thanks to the recent restoration, the villa has a sound system, laundry facilities and Wi-Fi.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: The villa and experience was everything it was described. Very private, exclusive, peaceful and quite beautiful. The chef experience alone was amazing. Very pleased overall.

We had a wonderful stay at the villa. The property was outstanding and the views were spectacular. Emmanuel does a great job looking after the property and took care of all our needs. Francois and Heidi spoilt us with great food and service.

item.title: Villa Il Palmeto
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Villa Il Palmeto is a stunning luxury villa located in the coveted Castelsardo area of Sardinia. Situated in the Gulf of Asinara, Castelsardo is the main town of the Anglona. A place of natural beauty, traditions and wonderful works of art, this medieval town makes a charming place to spend a holiday between the sea and a rich history in an idyllic climate.
The magnificent infinity swimming pool is shaped like a piano. The deck comes equipped with ample loungers and the garden and trees surrounding you will help put your mind at ease. The adjacent outdoor hot tub makes a great place to soothe any sore muscles??perfect for after the flight. A barbeque sets the tone for good food, wine and laughs. You can also keep on top of your regular workouts at the fitness facility offered at Villa Il Palmeto.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: We would like to extend our thanks and gratitude for having stayed in your "Marvelous Villa" :) Seems Everything's Perfect! The Bed, Toilets, The Pool, Unbelievable :) My daughters really enjoyed being in front of the apple tv & my son cant get up from the pool.. Thanks to Indri, Gusty n Desy For All Delicious Meals, How to Presenting, Feels like we Have Dinner in 5 Stars Hotel..

item.title: Villa Sullivan
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Brimming with personality, Villa Sullivan huddles into the Parian hillside, overlooking acres of bountiful olive yards. The villas?? enviable position offers views across a landscape dotted with pretty whitewash houses and out to sea, where you will find the island??s miniature neighbor, Antiparos. Just 1km from the villa lies popular Farangas beach. Venture just a little further for quaint fishing villages Ageria and Aliki.
Cozily tucked among higgledy dry-stone walls and native plants, sits a comfy outdoor couch paired with a well-placed coffee table. Here you will find a little pocket of peace with postcard views, perfect for a laid back breakfast.

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: This is a private Owner/Agent note thats not visible on the front end.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Of all the possible places I could have ended up in, I'm so happy that I ended up at Guy's villa! Spacious, clean, almost makes you feel a little guilty for living in such a beautiful place, but the guilt soon passes and what starts out as a place you've never been to, quickly turns into your home. The staff are super helpful, friendly and attentive and nothing is ever too much trouble. As I was traveling on my own, I was ready for a certain amount of loneliness along the way, but if Pina is near, no one could ever feel lonely or uncared for. I left there, hugging every staff member I could find and promising I'd be back. Just book it! You're welcome :)

item.title: La Veduta di Vertine
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Set on a beautiful hilltop in the Chianti Classico region, the spacious five-bedroom villa includes both a main house and guest cottage, two kitchens and four acres of land, so there??s room for the whole family or a group of friends. A location within walking distance of Gaiole in Chianti and driving distance of Florence means it??s easy to explore the region.
The villa provides both the privacy of a home and hotel-worthy amenities. There are four acres of olive groves and lawns to stroll, a bocce court, billiards room, several terraces and a heated infinity pool with plenty of lounge chairs. Gather eggs from the property??s chickens and produce from its fruit trees, prepare dinner on the outdoor grill or pizza oven, select a vintage from the wine cellar and dine at the table in the stone courtyard.

item.title: Villa Pep Simo Sea
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded: Perched dramatically on the hillside overlooking the dazzling Mediterranean, Villa Pep Simo Sea exudes an air of grandeur and opulence. From the impressive curved terrace you can enjoy a birds-eye view of the picturesque houses below. In the embrace of its turquoise infinity pool you will feel part of the sparkling sea beyond. Recline on an enticing sun lounger and the Ibizan sun will help soothe away your everyday cares and concerns. At Villa Pep Simo Sea you??ll be transported to the height of luxury and relaxation.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: My wife and I absolutely loved the villa. It's beautiful, spacious, has views, and just a lovely space to relax in. The host was good with communication and the on site manager was helpful with local information. The place is better suited to people who enjoy staying in the villa a fair bit as a) it's so nice you don't want to leave and b) it 15 plus mins taxi to Canggu/Echo Beach where the restaurants are.

Fabulous villa with serene ambient and peaceful location, We love everything about this villa, we stayed for 3 nights and everything went smooth and well. Arta very helping us from the moment we came till back,and yes Pina also very lovely and help us to make our stay better. We definitely come again and will recommend to others.

item.title: Camporempoli
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
With its arched doorways, stone exterior and beautifully restored interiors, villa Camporempoli is a charming hideaway. Its secluded location in the hills outside Siena and panoramic views of the Chianti area offer peace and quiet. A pool, outdoor dining area and garden are your own piece of the Tuscan countryside to enjoy.
The house is laid out around a central patio, so the airy living areas open to the patio on one side and the garden on the other. Step onto the terrace at the front of the house to take in the views, or duck under a vine-covered pergola to enjoy a glass of wine at the marble dining table. There??s a barbecue and a pool with a large shallow end perfect for children, not to mention an overflow effect and view of the hills. See if you can spot the villa??s resident cat amid the lush landscaping.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: After spending a few days in seclusion of the villa was a great change of pace. The staff and host made us feel very welcome and comfortable. The property was amazing, and allowed us to relax and enjoy our time.

The pictures do not do this villa justice. This is a truly spectacular place to stay. Host Pina and her staff could not do enough to accommodate us. What makes this place truly special is that unlike many other places in Bali, the surrounds of this villa are both beautiful and unspoiled. The beach is literally 5 minutes walk away, however the lagoon swimming pool and leisure beds provided significant incentive not to leave!

wp:commentmeta.wp:meta_value: Better than a suite in a 5 star resort!

item.title: Villa Ada
item.dc:creator: demo
item.content:encoded:
With views of both Tuscany and Umbria, a getaway to villa Ada will give you some perspective. The secluded seven-bedroom villa offers plenty of privacy, too, with a rural setting and separate accommodations for two families or larger groups of friends. But it’s not isolated; its location just outside Perugia makes it easy to visit the region’s cities and towns.
The property is comprised of a main house and separate annex that have their own kitchens, living areas and bedrooms, but share a pool. There’s a grill, an outdoor dining area shaded by a rose-covered pergola and plenty of outdoor furniture in which to relax. Guests can arrange to use a shared tennis court, and indulgences like massages and yoga classes are available at extra cost. Even though you’ll be staying in the country, stay connected via the property’s Wi-Fi access.
